==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: High-toned
<hw>High"-toned`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>High
in tone or sound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Elevated; high-principled; honorable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In whose <qex>high-toned</qex> impartial mind⟦br⟧
Degrees of mortal rank and state⟦br⟧
Seem objects of indifferent weight.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Scott.</qau></rj></p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>pretentious, pompous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>High-top</ent>⟦br⟧
